      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISSISSIPPI MORN (5) showed good early dash and led throughout to score by 0.7 lengths last time out over 1075m at Thangool. Good record at this journey with four wins and two minor placings from nine starts. The one to beat. JUST SUPER (1) was well supported when resuming last time out over 1100m at Springsure and proved too strong, scoring by 5 lengths. Generally runs well second-up and is among the winning hopes again. THE SQUIRE (4) has not appeared since he finished fifth over 1200m at Thangool on November 29. Makes plenty of appeal fresh. WRITTLE (2) has a decent strike rate so is capable of better than he has shown of late, including a last start ninth at Doomben. Finds a more suitable race and is in the mix.",
